red prior to and daily during clofarabine therapy, and administration discontinued immediately if substantial increases (e.g., grade 3 or higher) in creatinine, liver enzymes, or bilirubin are noted.', 'Synergism, Excretion', 'Fluorouracil, Mercaptopurine, Cladribine, Trifluridine, Floxuridine, Gemcitabine, Nelarabine, Cytarabine, Fludarabine, Decitabine, Azacitidine, More', 'Acetylsalicylic acid, Salicylic acid, Choline salicylate, Ziconotide', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/69969/', '[1] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[2] "Product Information. Clolar (clofarabine)." sanofi-aventis, Bridgewater, NJ.', 1767369485);
